        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer22249161" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11867896729083177322">Pema Chodron takes Tich Naht Hahn&apos;s Zen Buddhist wisdom and makes it readable. No totally obscure allegories or fragments of wisdom to decode for meaning. She is straight from the heart, speaks of her experience, and translates the traditional Buddhist teachings into an every day accessible language and practice. I reference Tich Naht Hahn, but she is actually from a different school of Buddhism under Tringpah Ringpoche.<br/><br/></span>
  <span id="freeText11867896729083177322" style="display:none">Pema Chodron takes Tich Naht Hahn's Zen Buddhist wisdom and makes it readable. No totally obscure allegories or fragments of wisdom to decode for meaning. She is straight from the heart, speaks of her experience, and translates the traditional Buddhist teachings into an every day accessible language and practice. I reference Tich Naht Hahn, but she is actually from a different school of Buddhism under Tringpah Ringpoche.<br /><br /></span>
