    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_7440452" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/7440452" />
    <a title="Cassidy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/316107-cassidy"><img alt="Cassidy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1188311470p2/316107.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/7440452?book_show_action=true">Oct 08, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cassidy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cassidy" href="/user/show/316107-cassidy">Cassidy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer7440452" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11231309362611147035">I would not call myself a particularly &quot;spiritual&quot; person, but someone who I respect deeply for his ability to treat all things with an even temper gave me this book. While I can&apos;t say that I practice this all the time (ha ha ha), I respect the idea that 1) it&apos;s important to accept yourself, including all of your glorious faults, 2) all things can teach you something, and 3) we should all try to be a little gentler with ourselves and with others.</span>
  <span id="freeText11231309362611147035" style="display:none">I would not call myself a particularly "spiritual" person, but someone who I respect deeply for his ability to treat all things with an even temper gave me this book. While I can't say that I practice this all the time (ha ha ha), I respect the idea that 1) it's important to accept yourself, including all of your glorious faults, 2) all things can teach you something, and 3) we should all try to be a little gentler with ourselves and with others.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11231309362611147035" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


