<div id="review_2194739402" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2194739402" />
    <a title="Nikki" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/65298226-nikki"><img alt="Nikki" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1498770901p2/65298226.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2194739402?book_show_action=true">Nov 25, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nikki" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nikki" href="/user/show/65298226-nikki">Nikki</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9781590307939" href="/book/show/7292976-the-wisdom-of-no-escape">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/65298226-nikki?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/65298226-nikki?shelf=advice">advice</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2194739402" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3167604485159427384">I borrowed this book of brief talks (given during a month-long Buddhist meditation retreat) from the library after seeing it recommended on <a href='https://www.brainpickings.org/2015/01/19/pema-chodron-the-wisdom-of-no-escape/' rel='nofollow noopener'>brainpickings.org</a>, and although it was very short, I enjoyed reading it slowly, rationing myself to one talk daily to give myself time to reflect on each section. I liked the down-to-earth and humorous (often self-deprecating) style, and found it generally persuasive (in the abstract, anyway...). She quotes her teacher, Chögyam Trungpa, Rinpoche, as saying t</span>
  <span id="freeText3167604485159427384" style="display:none">I borrowed this book of brief talks (given during a month-long Buddhist meditation retreat) from the library after seeing it recommended on <a href="https://www.brainpickings.org/2015/01/19/pema-chodron-the-wisdom-of-no-escape/" rel="nofollow noopener">brainpickings.org</a>, and although it was very short, I enjoyed reading it slowly, rationing myself to one talk daily to give myself time to reflect on each section. I liked the down-to-earth and humorous (often self-deprecating) style, and found it generally persuasive (in the abstract, anyway...). She quotes her teacher, Chögyam Trungpa, Rinpoche, as saying that the goal of meditation practice is:<br /><blockquote>
  <i>"A complete acceptance and openness to all situations and emotions and to all people, experiencing everything totally without reservations or blockages, so that one never withdraws or centralizes into oneself."</i>
</blockquote> I also appreciated the following statement:<br /><blockquote>
  <i>"Life's work is to wake up, to let the things that enter into the circle wake you up rather than put you to sleep. The only way to do this is to open, be curious, and develop some sense of sympathy for everything that comes along, to get to know its nature and let it teach you what it will."</i>
</blockquote></span>
  <a data-text-id="3167604485159427384" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


